Package net.chwthewke.hamcrest.matchers

This package exposes the implementation entry point EquivalenceMatchers which has methods to create Equivalences from equivalence specifications.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Equivalence<T> This interface defines a relation over a type, computed and described with hamcrest matchers.
EquivalenceSpecification<T> The EquivalenceSpecification interface is a marker interface used as a convenience in type parameter resolution.
 

Class Summary
EquivalenceMatchers This class has some factory methods to create Equivalence instances from equivalence specifications (i.e. classes annotated with EquivalenceSpecificationOn).
 

Package net.chwthewke.hamcrest.matchers Description

This package exposes the implementation entry point EquivalenceMatchers which has methods to create Equivalences from equivalence specifications.
